{"heading":"Jesus preaches the Sermon on the Mount—Its teachings replace and transcend some aspects of the law of Moses—All are commanded to be perfect like their Father in Heaven.","number":5,"verseCount":48,"verses":[[1,[["And",["study-note-ref","a",[["3 Ne. 12:1 (1–48)","bofm/3-ne/12.1"],"."]]]," seeing the multitudes, he went up into a mountain: and when he was set, his disciples came unto him:"]],[2,["And he opened his mouth, and taught them, saying,"]],[3,[["Blessed",["study-note-ref","a",["The Latin beatus is the basis of the English “beatitude,” meaning “to be fortunate,” “to be happy,” or “to be blessed.” ",["TG Blessing","tg/blessing"],"."]]]," ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," the ",["poor in spirit",["study-note-ref","b",["IE poor in pride, humble in spirit; ",["3 Ne. 12:3","bofm/3-ne/12.3"]," reads “… the poor in spirit who come unto me.” ",["James 2:5 (1–9)","nt/james/2.5"],"; ",["D&C 56:18 (18–20)","dc-testament/dc/56.18"],"; ",["88:17","dc-testament/dc/88.17"],". ",["TG Contrite Heart","tg/contrite-heart"],"; ",["Humility","tg/humility"],"; ",["Poor in Spirit","tg/poor-in-spirit"],"."]]],": for theirs is the ",["kingdom",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Kingdom of God, in Heaven","tg/kingdom-of-god-in-heaven"],"."]]]," of heaven."]],[4,["Blessed ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," they that ",["mourn",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Mourning","tg/mourning"],"; ",["Sorrow","tg/sorrow"],"."]]],": for they shall be ",["comforted",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Comfort","tg/comfort"],"."]]],"."]],[5,["Blessed ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," the ",["meek",["study-note-ref","a",["GR gentle, forgiving, or benevolent; the Hebrew in ",["Ps. 37:11","ot/ps/37.11"]," characterizes as the humble those who have suffered. ",["TG Meek","tg/meek"],"."]]],": for they shall inherit the ",["earth",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Earth, Destiny of","tg/earth-destiny-of"],"."]]],"."]],[6,["Blessed ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," they which do ",["hunger",["study-note-ref","a",[["3 Ne. 12:6","bofm/3-ne/12.